```java
class Student extends Person {
    private String school;

    public Student(String name, int age, String school) {
        super(name, age);
        this.school = school;
    }

    @Override
    public void introduce() {
        super.introduce();
        System.out.println("I study at " + school);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student student = new Student("Bob", 20, "Harvard");
        student.introduce();
    }
}
```

This example demonstrates inheritance by creating a `Student` class that extends the `Person` class. The `Student` class adds a school field and overrides the introduce method to include school information.

